'''Oxhill''' is a [[village]] in South [[Warwickshire]], [[England]], off the [[A422 road]] between [[Stratford-upon-Avon]] and [[Banbury]]. It lies in the administrative [[Districts of England|district]] of [[Stratford-on-Avon (district)|Stratford-upon-Avon]] in the area known as the [[Vale of the Red Horse]]. The village is mentioned in the [[Domesday Book]] as "Octeselve" and has a [[12th century]] [[church]] dedicated to [[Saint Lawrence]].

